 Quant Engine

A modular **Quantitative Trading Engine** built from scratch using Python.

Designed to be **backtestable, extensible**, and educational â€” this system models real-world trading architecture including:

-  Historical data handling
-  Strategy layer (momentum-based to start)
-  Execution simulator (vectorized backtester)
-  Risk management (Sharpe, VaR, Kelly)
-  Performance visualization

> Built by [@panwarparth](https://github.com/panwarparth) | GitHub project URL: [quant_engine](https://github.com/panwarparth/quant_engine)


 ðŸš€ Features

| Module         | Description                                                    |
|----------------|----------------------------------------------------------------|
| `data_handler` | Generates or loads price data (synthetic for now)             |
| `momentum`     | Moving Average crossover strategy (long-only)                 |
| `backtester`   | Calculates equity curve, metrics, risk stats                  |
| `kelly`        | Kelly Criterion sizing for continuous + binary returns        |
| `run_example`  | Script to demonstrate full pipeline and save equity plot      |

